  Let $r$ be the annual interest rate.  Then the investment grows to $1000(1+r)^3=1225$.  Solving for $r$, we find $r=\sqrt[3]{\frac{1225}{1000}}-1\approx\boxed{7\%}$.  (Note that this is the same as the annual interest rate of 7% that Mr. Madoff used to make his fortune.)  (We could have also solved for $r$ by taking the cube root of both sides and then subtracting 1.)  [asy]
